If you have killed one of these you can most likely kill any of them.<br>
<br>
Settle in for a long fight overall.  Depending on your tactics will determine whether one is harder than the other.  <br>
<br>
Keeping guards clear in IV room can make for a more intense fight.  Not aggroing guards at all makes it a very easy fight.  You choose how you do it, if you can control where you fly.<br>
<br>
For Grieg's control where you get thrown too using tactics and experience you gained from attempting him and learning how his aoe works.<br>
<br>
For THO... use his aoes against him.  Clear the guards quickly and you have all the time in the world to finish off THO.<br>
<br>
Each fight has major annoyances in it's own ways, but they are all about on par with each other.<br>
<br>
I have yet to fight a duel wielding IV, so I don't know how that compares.<br>
